 \"a gentle reservation\", \"from\": 3519, \"to\": 3539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, true enough.\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3558, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But his gray suit and Roman collar seemed to dilute the effect.\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3581, \"end\": 3593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clerical_collar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roman collar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clerical_collar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clerical_collar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his gray suit\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3576}, {\"ngram\": \"the effect\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Call me old fashioned, but a priest in a gray suit does not make hearts race as does the sight of St. Francis Xavier in cassock holding high the cross.Shall we dare a more provocative question?If the Holy Roman Church were as strong now as it was in the times of the Roman persecutions, the Middle Ages, or in the pontificates of Blessed Pius IX or St. Pius X, would this kind of blasphemy have shown its face?\", \"from\": 3623, \"to\": 4033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3828, \"end\": 3833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.8749228650200666, \"rank\": 0.07988470748590021, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 3890, \"end\": 3895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.8749228650200666, \"rank\": 0.07988470748590021, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 3961, \"end\": 3968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2483260313899126e-17, \"text\": \"Pius IX\", \"