urce/Pope_Pius_IX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a priest\", \"from\": 18082, \"to\": 18090}, {\"ngram\": \"a gray suit\", \"from\": 18094, \"to\": 18105}, {\"ngram\": \"hearts\", \"from\": 18120, \"to\": 18126}, {\"ngram\": \"the sight\", \"from\": 18140, \"to\": 18149}, {\"ngram\": \"St. Francis Xavier\", \"from\": 18153, \"to\": 18171}, {\"ngram\": \"cassock\", \"from\": 18175, \"to\": 18182}, {\"ngram\": \"the cross\", \"from\": 18196, \"to\": 18205}, {\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 18305, \"to\": 18314}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle Ages\", \"from\": 18342, \"to\": 18357}, {\"ngram\": \"the pontificates\", \"from\": 18365, \"to\": 18381}, {\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 18422, \"to\": 18431}, {\"ngram\": \"blasphemy\", \"from\": 18435, \"to\": 18444}, {\"ngram\": \"its face\", \"from\": 18456, \"to\": 18464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The secular world would not have dared.\", \"from\": 18466, \"to\": 18505, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The secular world\", \"from\": 18466, \"to\": 18483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, those historical periods dealt Mother Church its share of ignominy, but never did they threaten the very cornerstone of her doctrinal patrimony.\", \"from\": 18506, \"to\": 18655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18542, \"end\": 18555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother_church\", \"score\": 0.9999910714232797, \"rank\": 8.928656386896056e-06, \"text\": \"Mother Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother_church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother_church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those historical periods\", \"from\": 18511, \"to\": 18535}, {\"ngram\": \"its share\", \"from\": 18556, \"to\": 18565}, {\"ngram\": \"ignominy\", \"from\": 18569, \"to\": 18577}, {\"ngram\": \"the very cornerstone\", \"from\": 18607, \"to\": 18627}, {\"ngram\": \"her doctrinal patrimony\", \"from\": 18631, \"to\": 18654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"None would have mocked the very foundations of the moral law, indeed of the divinely established order of sexual difference.\", \"from\": 18656, \"to\": 18780, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"None\", \"from\": 18656, \"to\": 18660}, {\"ngram\": \"the very foundations\", \"from\": 18679, \"to\": 18699}, {\"ngram\": \"the moral law\", \"from\": 18703, \"to\": 18716}, {\"ngram\": \"the divinely established order\", \"from\": 18728, \"to\": 18758}, {\"ngram\": \"sexual difference\", \"from\": 18762, \"to\": 18779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And if they had, they would have been met by all the ferocity of her thundering condemnations.If the Holy Roman Church were as strong now as it was in the times of the Roman persecutions, the Middle Ages, or in the pontificates of Blessed Pius IX or St. Pius X, would this kind of blasphemy have shown its face?Tweet ThisThose manic forces were kept at bay by the might of the Church.\", \"from\": 18781, \"to\": 19165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 18887, \"end\": 18892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.8408879383311841, \"rank\": 0.18920124892820603, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 18949, \"end\": 18954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"score\": 0.8408879383311841, \"rank\": 0.18920124892820603, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 19020, \"end\": 19027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.513480450564975e-15, \"text\": \"Pius IX\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the ferocity\", \"from\": 18826, \"to\": 18842}, {\"ngram\": \"her thundering condemnations\", \"from\": 18846, \"to\": 18874}, {\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 18932, \"to\": 18941}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle Ages\", \"from\": 18969, \"to\": 18984}, {\"ngram\": \"the pontificates\", \"from\": 18992, \"to\": 19008}, {\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 19049, \"to\": 19058}, {\"ngram\": \"blasphemy\", \"from\": 19062, \"to\": 19071}, {\"ngram\": \"its face?Tweet\", \"from\": 19083, \"to\": 19097}, {\"ngram\": \"ThisThose manic forces\", \"from\": 19098, \"to\": 19120}, {\"ngram\": \"bay\", \"from\": 19134, \"to\": 19137}, {\"ngram\": \"the might\", \"from\": 19141, \"to\": 19150}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 19154, \"to\": 19164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that doctrinal roar bellowed with no uncertainty, and with one universal voice.\", \"from\": 19166, \"to\": 19249, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"And that doctrinal roar\", \"from\": 19166, \"to\": 19189}, {\"ngram\": \"no uncertainty\", \"from\": 19204, \"to\": 19218}, {\"ngram\": \"one universal voice\", \"from\": 19229, \"to\": 19248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The World would find no cracks in the solidity of the Church's voice in those sturdier days.\", \"from\": 19250, \"to\": 19342, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The World\", \"from\": 19250, \"to\": 19259}, {\"ngram\": \"no cracks\", \"from\": 19271, \"to\": 19280}, {\"ngram\": \"the solidity\", \"from\": 19284, \"to\": 19296}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 19300, \"to\": 19318}, {\"ngram\": \"those sturdier days\", \"from\": 19322, \"to\": 19341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contrary voices would indeed bay, but they had no illusions about the impregnable bastions of the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 19343, \"to\": 19457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19441, \"end\": 19456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999936288646181, \"rank\": 6.295024999527966e-06, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Contrary voices\", \"from\": 19343, \"to\": 19358}, {\"ngram\": \"no illusions\", \"from\": 19390, \"to\": 19402}, {\"ngram\": \"the impregnable bastions\", \"from\": 19409, \"to\": 19433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They might have found shelter in a renegade priest or shepherd here or there, but those of that ilk were conspicuous in their paucity.Blasphemy on such a grand scale as the Opening Ceremonies of the Paris Olympics would have been unthinkable.\", \"from\": 19458, \"to\": 19700, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"shelter\", \"from\": 19480, \"to\": 19487}, {\"ngram\": \"a renegade priest\", \"from\": 19491, \"to\": 19508}, {\"ngram\": \"shepherd\", \"from\": 19512, \"to\": 19520}, {\"ngram\": \"that ilk\", \"from\": 19549, \"to\": 19557}, {\"ngram\": \"their paucity\", \"from\": 19578, \"to\": 19591}, {\"ngram\": \"Blasphemy\", \"from\": 19592, \"to\": 19601}, {\"ngram\": \"such a grand scale\", \"from\": 19605, \"to\": 19623}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 19627, \"to\": 19649}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 19653, \"to\": 19671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, Napolean kidnapped Pope Pius VII in 1809, dragging him across the Alps in precarious health to Fontainebleau.\", \"from\": 19701, \"to\": 19815, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19801, \"end\": 19814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"score\": 0.9962463418614256, \"rank\": 0.0037677972716039392, \"text\": \"Fontainebleau\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pope Pius VII\", \"from\": 19725, \"to\": 19738}, {\"ngram\": \"the Alps\", \"from\": 19768, \"to\": 19776}, {\"ngram\": \"precarious health\", \"from\": 19780, \"to\": 19797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Italian armies captured Rome in 1859, forcing Blessed Pius IX to flee the Eternal City to the city of Gaeta.\", \"from\": 19816, \"to\": 19932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19824, \"end\": 19831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.7115898669815036, \"rank\": 0.321185025007323, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 19848, \"end\": 19852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9703207458593173, \"rank\": 0.028117972766511002, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 19926, \"end\": 19931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"score\": 0.9999999993063966, \"rank\": 6.935520120702506e-10, \"text\": \"Gaeta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Blessed Pius IX\", \"from\": 19870, \"to\": 19885}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eternal City\", \"from\": 19894, \"to\": 19910}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 19914, \"to\": 19922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But all these depredations could not approach the collapse that the Opening Ceremonies presage.\", \"from\": 19933, \"to\": 20028, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all these depredations\", \"from\": 19937, \"to\": 19959}, {\"ngram\": \"the collapse\", \"from\": 19979, \"to\": 19991}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 19997, \"to\": 20019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Church was assaulted and the popes harassed, the foundations of human dignity and Western Civilization were not threatened.\", \"from\": 20029, \"to\": 20162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20121, \"end\": 20141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\