platter\", \"from\": 20554, \"to\": 20570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How else to interpret Archbishop Paglia, president of the Pontifical Academy for Life, defending the Olympic Last Supper depiction \\\"as revealing a profound question: everyone, absolutely everyone, wants to sit at that table where Jesus gives life to everyone and teaches love.\", \"from\": 20572, \"to\": 20848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20594, \"end\": 20604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9986941707365229, \"rank\": 0.0010534093412937896, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 20802, \"end\": 20807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9995724910099234, \"rank\": 0.00042769165394400345, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 20613, \"to\": 20622}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pontifical Academy\", \"from\": 20626, \"to\": 20648}, {\"ngram\": \"Life\", \"from\": 20653, \"to\": 20657}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Last Supper depiction\", \"from\": 20669, \"to\": 20702}, {\"ngram\": \"a profound question\", \"from\": 20717, \"to\": 20736}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 20738, \"to\": 20746}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely everyone\", \"from\": 20748, \"to\": 20767}, {\"ngram\": \"that table\", \"from\": 20785, \"to\": 20795}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 20814, \"to\": 20818}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 20822, \"to\": 20830}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 20843, \"to\": 20847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is ambiguity and cowardice writ large.Mankind's only wallagainst the encroachment of the barbarian is the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 20848, \"to\": 20976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20960, \"end\": 20975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999991278917088, \"rank\": 8.721051333492954e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ambiguity\", \"from\": 20857, \"to\": 20866}, {\"ngram\": \"writ\", \"from\": 20881, \"to\": 20885}, {\"ngram\": \"Mankind\", \"from\": 20892, \"to\": 20899}, {\"ngram\": \"the encroachment\", \"from\": 20919, \"to\": 20935}, {\"ngram\": \"the barbarian\", \"from\": 20939, \"to\": 20952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She alone can return a voice to the oppressed of the Woke Leviathan.In A.D. 452, it was only one year after Pope Leo the Great valiantly defended the hypostatic union of Christ our Savior against the heretic Eutyches.With that monumental task barely completed, he confronted still another crisis besetting the Roman world: the attack of Attila the Hun.\", \"from\": 20977, \"to\": 21329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21030, \"end\": 21034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.0140733383104605e-17, \"text\": \"Woke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\"}, {\"begin\": 21090, \"end\": 21093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"score\": 0.9993567002511116, \"rank\": 0.0006436503786214178, \"text\": \"Leo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\"}, {\"begin\": 21287, \"end\": 21292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9967431231542826, \"rank\": 0.00300437000478826, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 21314, \"end\": 21320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.0671628213576585e-30, \"text\": \"Attila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a voice\", \"from\": 20998, \"to\": 21005}, {\"ngram\": \"the oppressed\", \"from\": 21009, \"to\": 21022}, {\"ngram\": \"A.D.\", \"from\": 21048, \"to\": 21052}, {\"ngram\": \"the Great\", \"from\": 21094, \"to\": 21103}, {\"ngram\": \"the hypostatic union\", \"from\": 21123, \"to\": 21143}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 21147, \"to\": 21153}, {\"ngram\": \"our Savior\", \"from\": 21154, \"to\": 21164}, {\"ngram\": \"the heretic Eutyches\", \"from\": 21173, \"to\": 21193}, {\"ngram\": \"that monumental task\", \"from\": 21199, \"to\": 21219}, {\"ngram\": \"another crisis\", \"from\": 21258, \"to\": 21272}, {\"ngram\": \"the attack\", \"from\": 21300, \"to\": 21310}, {\"ngram\": \"the Hun\", \"from\": 21321, \"to\": 21328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His frightful hordes had decimated much of the former Roman Empire, with its legacy of high civilization and culture.\", \"from\": 21330, \"to\": 21447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21384, \"end\": 21396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9974784370755385, \"rank\": 0.0025236603132205, \"text\": \"Roman Empire\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His frightful hordes\", \"from\": 21330, \"to\": 21350}, {\"ngram\": \"its legacy\", \"from\": 21403, \"to\": 21413}, {\"ngram\": \"high civilization\", \"from\": 21417, \"to\": 21434}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 21439, \"to\": 21446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now that barbarian was at the very gates of Rome.\", \"from\": 21448, \"to\": 21497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21492, \"end\": 21496, \"title\": \"http: