to\": 39631}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The World would find no cracks in the solidity of the Church's voice in those sturdier days.\", \"from\": 39633, \"to\": 39725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The World\", \"from\": 39633, \"to\": 39642}, {\"ngram\": \"no cracks\", \"from\": 39654, \"to\": 39663}, {\"ngram\": \"the solidity\", \"from\": 39667, \"to\": 39679}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 39683, \"to\": 39701}, {\"ngram\": \"those sturdier days\", \"from\": 39705, \"to\": 39724}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contrary voices would indeed bay, but they had no illusions about the impregnable bastions of the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 39726, \"to\": 39840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 39824, \"end\": 39839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999987465929404, \"rank\": 1.2398044039705957e-06, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Contrary voices\", \"from\": 39726, \"to\": 39741}, {\"ngram\": \"no illusions\", \"from\": 39773, \"to\": 39785}, {\"ngram\": \"the impregnable bastions\", \"from\": 39792, \"to\": 39816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They might have found shelter in a renegade priest or shepherd here or there, but those of that ilk were conspicuous in their paucity.Blasphemy on such a grand scale as the Opening Ceremonies of the Paris Olympics would have been unthinkable.\", \"from\": 39841, \"to\": 40083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"shelter\", \"from\": 39863, \"to\": 39870}, {\"ngram\": \"a renegade priest\", \"from\": 39874, \"to\": 39891}, {\"ngram\": \"shepherd\", \"from\": 39895, \"to\": 39903}, {\"ngram\": \"that ilk\", \"from\": 39932, \"to\": 39940}, {\"ngram\": \"their paucity\", \"from\": 39961, \"to\": 39974}, {\"ngram\": \"Blasphemy\", \"from\": 39975, \"to\": 39984}, {\"ngram\": \"such a grand scale\", \"from\": 39988, \"to\": 40006}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 40010, \"to\": 40032}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 40036, \"to\": 40054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, Napolean kidnapped Pope Pius VII in 1809, dragging him across the Alps in precarious health to Fontainebleau.\", \"from\": 40084, \"to\": 40198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 40184, \"end\": 40197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"score\": 0.9747290121244662, \"rank\": 0.02592616664473476, \"text\": \"Fontainebleau\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pope Pius VII\", \"from\": 40108, \"to\": 40121}, {\"ngram\": \"the Alps\", \"from\": 40151, \"to\": 40159}, {\"ngram\": \"precarious health\", \"from\": 40163, \"to\": 40180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Italian armies captured Rome in 1859, forcing Blessed Pius IX to flee the Eternal City to the city of Gaeta.\", \"from\": 40199, \"to\": 40315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 40207, \"end\": 40214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9035690354186583, \"rank\": 0.05535887154299078, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 40309, \"end\": 40314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"score\": 0.9999999997224904, \"rank\": 2.7753627201267047e-10, \"text\": \"Gaeta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rome\", \"from\": 40231, \"to\": 40235}, {\"ngram\": \"Blessed Pius IX\", \"from\": 40253, \"to\": 40268}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eternal City\", \"from\": 40277, \"to\": 40293}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 40297, \"to\": 40305}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But all these depredations could not approach the collapse that the Opening Ceremonies presage.\", \"from\": 40316, \"to\": 40411, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all these depredations\", \"from\": 40320, \"to\": 40342}, {\"ngram\": \"the collapse\", \"from\": 40362, \"to\": 40374}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 40380, \"to\": 40402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Church was assaulted and the popes harassed, the foundations of human dignity and Western Civilization were not threatened.\", \"from\": 40412, \"to\": 40545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 40504, \"end\": 40524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.9500285459557819, \"rank\": 0.05259995002990544, \"text\": \"Western Civilization\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 40418, \"to\": 40428}, {\"ngram\": \"the popes\", \"from\": 40447, \"to\": 40456}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundations\", \"from\": 40467, \"to\": 40482}, {\"ngram\": \"human dignity\", \"from\": 40486, \"to\": 40499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Church, even with her popes in captivity, would see to that.Enemies of all that is good and true and beautiful have found their opening in the decades-long attenuation of the Church's voice.\", \"from\": 40546, \"to\": 40740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Church\", \"from\": 40546, \"to\": 40556}, {\"ngram\": \"her popes\", \"from\": 40568, \"to\": 40577}, {\"ngram\": \"captivity\", \"from\": 40581, \"to\": 40590}, {\"ngram\": \"Enemies\", \"from\": 40610, \"to\": 40617}, {\"ngram\": \"their opening\", \"from\": 40672, \"to\": 40685}, {\"ngram\": \"the decades-long attenuation\", \"from\": 40689, \"to\": 40717}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 40721, \"to\": 40739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have seen all too clearly the Church's d\\u00e9tente with the spirit of the world and exploited a perfect opportunity.\", \"from\": 40741, \"to\": 40858, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church's d\\u00e9tente\", \"from\": 40772, \"to\": 40792}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 40798, \"to\": 40808}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 40812, \"to\": 40821}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect opportunity\", \"from\": 40836, \"to\": 40857}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the victory they awaited for so long, and now it was handed to them on a silver platter.\", \"from\": 40859, \"to\": 40954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the victory\", \"from\": 40866, \"to\": 40877}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver platter\", \"from\": 40937, \"to\": 40953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How else to interpret Archbishop Paglia, president of the Pontifical Academy for Life, defending the Olympic Last Supper depiction \\\"as revealing a profound question: everyone, absolutely everyone, wants to sit at that table where Jesus gives life to everyone and teaches love.\", \"from\": 40955, \"to\": 41231, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 40977, \"end\": 40987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.999590465449663, \"rank\": 0.00018883561386382662, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 41185, \"end\": 41190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.6999119151289488, \"rank\": 0.4287484320680793, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 40996, \"to\": 41005}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pontifical Academy\", \"from\": 41009, \"to\": 41031}, {\"ngram\": \"Life\", \"from\": 41036, \"to\": 41040}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Last Supper depiction\", \"from\": 41052, \"to\": 41085}, {\"ngram\