m\": 62671, \"to\": 62684}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She alone can return a voice to the oppressed of the Woke Leviathan.In A.D. 452, it was only one year after Pope Leo the Great valiantly defended the hypostatic union of Christ our Savior against the heretic Eutyches.With that monumental task barely completed, he confronted still another crisis besetting the Roman world: the attack of Attila the Hun.\", \"from\": 62709, \"to\": 63061, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 62762, \"end\": 62766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.291230735885765e-16, \"text\": \"Woke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\"}, {\"begin\": 62822, \"end\": 62825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"score\": 0.9999844888821097, \"rank\": 1.5511288252685733e-05, \"text\": \"Leo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\"}, {\"begin\": 63019, \"end\": 63024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9954923038096594, \"rank\": 0.004522005895888266, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 63046, \"end\": 63052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.194777062409061e-30, \"text\": \"Attila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a voice\", \"from\": 62730, \"to\": 62737}, {\"ngram\": \"the oppressed\", \"from\": 62741, \"to\": 62754}, {\"ngram\": \"A.D.\", \"from\": 62780, \"to\": 62784}, {\"ngram\": \"the Great\", \"from\": 62826, \"to\": 62835}, {\"ngram\": \"the hypostatic union\", \"from\": 628