gram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 63743, \"to\": 63765}, {\"ngram\": \"AuthorFr\", \"from\": 63778, \"to\": 63786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John A. PerriconeFr.\", \"from\": 63788, \"to\": 63808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John A. PerriconeFr\", \"from\": 63788, \"to\": 63807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John A. Perricone, Ph.D., is an adjunct professor of philosophy at Iona University in New Rochelle, New York.\", \"from\": 63809, \"to\": 63918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 63876, \"end\": 63880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\", \"score\": 0.9661786228307152, \"rank\": 0.033868651622896304, \"text\": \"Iona\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\"}, {\"begin\": 63895, \"end\": 63917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Rochelle, New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\"}, {\"begin\": 63895, \"end\": 63917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Rochelle, New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John A. Perricone\", \"from\": 63809, \"to\": 63826}, {\"ngram\": \"Ph.D.\", \"from\": 63828, \"to\": 63833}, {\"ngram\": \"an adjunct professor\", \"from\": 63838, \"to\": 63858}, {\"ngram\": \"philosophy\", \"from\": 63862, \"to\": 63872}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His articles have appeared inSt.\", \"from\": 63919, \"to\": 63951, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His articles\", \"from\": 63919, \"to\": 63931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John's Law Review, The Latin Mass, New Oxford ReviewandThe Journal of Catholic Legal Studies.He can be reached atwww.fatherperricone.com.\", \"from\": 63952, \"to\": 64089, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John's Law Review\", \"from\": 63952, \"to\": 63969}, {\"ngram\": \"The Latin Mass\", \"from\": 63971, \"to\": 63985}, {\"ngram\": \"New Oxford ReviewandThe Journal\", \"from\": 63987, \"to\": 64018}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholic Legal Studies\", \"from\": 64022, \"to\": 64044}, {\"ngram\": \"atwww.fatherperricone.com\", \"from\": 64063, \"to\": 64088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shall we dare a more provocative question?If the Holy Roman Church were as strong now as it was in the times of the Roman persecutions, the Middle Ages, or in the pontificates of Blessed Pius IX or St. Pius X, would this kind of blasphemy have shown its face?\", \"from\": 64091, \"to\": 64350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 64145, \"end\": 64150, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.681221606397655, \"rank\": 0.4666640516518961, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 64207, \"end\": 64212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.681221606397655, \"rank\": 0.4666640516518961, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 64278, \"end\": 64285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3769363827412487e-16, \"text\": \"Pius IX\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 64190, \"to\": 64199}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle Ages\", \"from\": 64227, \"to\": 64242}, {\"ngram\": \"the pontificates\", \"from\": 64250, \"to\": 64266}, {\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 64307, \"to\": 64316}, {\"ngram\": \"blasphemy\", \"from\": 64320, \"to\": 64329}, {\"ngram\": \"its face\", \"from\": 64341, \"to\": 64349}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The secular world would not have dared.\", \"from\": 64351, \"to\": 64390, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The secular world\", \"from\": 64351, \"to\": 64368}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, those historical periods dealt Mother Church its share of ignominy, but never did they threaten the very cornerstone of her doctrinal patrimony.\", \"from\": 64391, \"to\": 64540, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 64427, \"end\": 64440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother_church\", \"score\": 0.9999963548113372, \"rank\": 3.64520199938889e-06, \"text\": \"Mother Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother_church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mother_church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those historical periods\", \"from\": 64396, \"to\": 64420}, {\"ngram\": \"its share\", \"from\": 64441, \"to\": 64450}, {\"ngram\": \"ignominy\", \"from\": 64454, \"to\": 64462}, {\"ngram\": \"the very cornerstone\", \"from\": 64492, \"to\": 64512}, {\"ngram\": \"her doctrinal patrimony\", \"from\": 64516, \"to\": 64539}]}, {\"sentence\": \"None would have mocked the very foundations of the moral law, indeed of the divinely established order of sexual difference.\", \"from\": 64541, \"to\": 64665, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"None\", \"from\": 64541, \"to\": 64545}, {\"ngram\": \"the very foundations\", \"from\": 64564, \"to\": 64584}, {\"ngram\": \"the moral law\", \"from\": 64588, \"to\": 64601}, {\"ngram\": \"the divinely established order\", \"from\": 64613, \"to\": 64643}, {\"ngram\": \"sexual difference\", \"from\": 64647, \"to\": 64664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And if they had, they would have been met by all the ferocity of her thundering condemnations.If the Holy Roman Church were as strong now as it was in the times of the Roman persecutions, the Middle Ages, or in the pontificates of Blessed Pius IX or St. Pius X, would this kind of blasphemy have shown its face?Tweet ThisThose manic forces were kept at bay by the might of the Church.\", \"from\": 64666, \"to\": 65050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 64772, \"end\": 64777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.681221606397655, \"rank\": 0.4666640516518961, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 64834, \"end\": 64839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.681221606397655, \"rank\": 0.4666640516518961, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 64905, \"end\": 64912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3769363827412487e-16, \"text\": \"Pius IX\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Pius_IX\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all the ferocity\", \"from\": 64711, \"to\": 64727}, {\"ngram\": \"her thundering condemnations\", \"from\": 64731, \"to\": 64759}, {\"ngram\": \"the times\", \"from\": 64817, \"to\": 64826}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle Ages\", \"from\": 64854, \"to\": 64869}, {\"ngram\": \"the pontificates\", \"from\": 64877, \"to\": 64893}, {\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 64934, \"to\": 64943}, {\"ngram\": \"blasphemy\", \"from\": 64947, \"to\": 64956}, {\"ngram\": \"its face?Tweet\", \"from\": 64968, \"to\": 64982}, {\"ngram\": \"ThisThose manic forces\", \"from\": 64983, \"to\": 65005}, {\"ngram\": \"bay\", \"from\": 65019, \"to\": 65022}, {\"ngram\": \"the might\", \"from\": 65026, \"to\": 65035}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 65039, \"to\": 65049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that doctrinal roar bellowed with no uncertainty, and with one universal voice.\", \"from\": 65051, \"to\": 65134, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"And that doctrinal roar\", \"from\": 65051, \"to\": 65074}, {\"ngram\": \"no uncertainty\", \"from\": 65089, \"to\": 65103}, {\"ngram\": \"one universal voice\", \"from\": 65114, \"to\": 65133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The World would find no cracks in the solidity of the Church's voice in those sturdier days.\", \"from\": 65135, \"to\": 65227, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The World\", \"from\": 65135, \"to\": 65144}, {\"ngram\": \"no cracks\", \"from\": 65156, \"to\": 65165}, {\"ngram\": \"the solidity\", \"from\": 65169, \"to\": 65181}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 65185, \"to\": 65203}, {\"ngram\": \"those sturdier days\", \"from\": 65207, \"to\": 65226}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contrary voices would indeed bay, but they had no illusions about the impregnable bastions of the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 65228, \"to\": 65342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 65326, \"end\": 65341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999979226521395, \"rank\": 1.7893095516892207e-06, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Contrary voices\", \"from\": 65228, \"to\": 65243}, {\"ngram\": \"no illusions\", \"from\": 65275, \"to\": 65287}, {\"ngram\": \"the impregnable bastions\", \"from\": 65294, \"to\": 65318}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They might have found shelter in a renegade priest or shepherd here or there, but those of that ilk were conspicuous in their paucity.Blasphemy on such a grand scale as the Opening Ceremonies of the Paris Olympics would have been unthinkable.\", \"from\": 65343, \"to\": 65585, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"shelter\", \"from\": 65365, \"to\": 65372}, {\"ngram\": \"a renegade priest\", \"from\": 65376, \"to\": 65393}, {\"ngram\": \"shepherd\", \"from\": 65397, \"to\": 65405}, {\"ngram\": \"that ilk\", \"from\": 65434, \"to\": 65442}, {\"ngram\": \"their paucity\", \"from\": 65463, \"to\": 65476}, {\"ngram\": \"Blasphemy\", \"from\": 65477, \"to\": 65486}, {\"ngram\": \"such a grand scale\", \"from\": 65490, \"to\": 65508}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 65512, \"to\": 65534}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 65538, \"to\": 65556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, Napolean kidnapped Pope Pius VII in 1809, dragging him across the Alps in precarious health to Fontainebleau.\", \"from\": 65586, \"to\": 65700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 65686, \"end\": 65699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"score\": 0.9961717282543867, \"rank\": 0.0038429812530537343, \"text\": \"Fontainebleau\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pope Pius VII\", \"from\": 65610, \"to\": 65623}, {\"ngram\": \"the Alps\", \"from\": 65653, \"to\": 65661}, {\"ngram\": \"precarious health\", \"from\": 65665, \"to\": 65682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Italian armies captured Rome in 1859, forcing Blessed Pius IX to flee the Eternal City to the city of Gaeta.\", \"from\": 65701, \"to\": 65817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 65709, \"end\": 65716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.8212157744436174, \"rank\": 0.14736111160833681, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 65811, \"end\": 65816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"score\": 0.9999999997318127, \"rank\": 2.68117761368277e-10, \"text\": \"Gaeta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Rome\", \"from\": 65733, \"to\": 65737}, {\"ngram\": \"Blessed Pius IX\", \"from\": 65755, \"to\": 65770}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eternal City\", \"from\": 65779, \"to\": 65795}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 65799, \"to\": 65807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But all these depredations could not approach the collapse that the Opening Ceremonies presage.\", \"from\": 65818, \"to\": 65913, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all these depredations\", \"from\": 65822, \"to\": 65844}, {\"ngram\": \"the collapse\", \"from\": 65864, \"to\": 65876}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 65882, \"to\": 65904}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Church was assaulted and the popes harassed, the foundations of human dignity and Western Civilization were not threatened.\", \"from\": 65914, \"to\": 66047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66006, \"end\": 66026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.7839701079557135, \"rank\": 0.27555883808841103, \"text\": \"Western Civilization\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 65920, \"to\": 65930}, {\"ngram\": \"the popes\", \"from\": 65949, \"to\": 65958}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundations\", \"from\": 65969, \"to\": 65984}, {\"ngram\": \"human dignity\", \"from\": 65988, \"to\": 66001}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Church, even with her popes in captivity, would see to that.Enemies of all that is good and true and beautiful have found their opening in the decades-long attenuation of the Church's voice.\", \"from\": 66048, \"to\": 66242, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Church\", \"from\": 66048, \"to\": 66058}, {\"ngram\": \"her popes\", \"from\": 66070, \"to\": 66079}, {\"ngram\": \"captivity\", \"from\": 66083, \"to\": 66092}, {\"ngram\": \"Enemies\", \"from\": 66112, \"to\": 66119}, {\"ngram\": \"their opening\", \"from\": 66174, \"to\": 66187}, {\"ngram\": \"the decades-long attenuation\", \"from\": 66191, \"to\": 66219}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 66223, \"to\": 66241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have seen all too clearly the Church's d\\u00e9tente with the spirit of the world and exploited a perfect opportunity.\", \"from\": 66243, \"to\": 66360, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church's d\\u00e9tente\", \"from\": 66274, \"to\": 66294}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 66300, \"to\": 66310}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 66314, \"to\": 66323}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect opportunity\", \"from\": 66338, \"to\": 66359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the victory they awaited for so long, and now it was handed to them on a silver platter.\", \"from\": 66361, \"to\": 66456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the victory\", \"from\": 66368, \"to\": 66379}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver platter\", \"from\": 66439, \"to\": 66455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How else to interpret Archbishop Paglia, president of the Pontifical Academy for Life, defending the Olympic Last Supper depiction \\\"as revealing a profound question: everyone, absolutely everyone, wants to sit at that table where Jesus gives life to everyone and teaches love.\", \"from\": 66457, \"to\": 66733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66479, \"end\": 66489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9995138667170311, \"rank\": 0.000458816879128475, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 66687, \"end\": 66692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9107167844489721, \"rank\": 0.09803617599281399, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 66498, \"to\": 66507}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pontifical Academy\", \"from\": 66511, \"to\": 66533}, {\"ngram\": \"Life\", \"from\": 66538, \"to\": 66542}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Last Supper depiction\", \"from\": 66554, \"to\": 66587}, {\"ngram\": \"a profound question\", \"from\": 66602, \"to\": 66621}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 66623, \"to\": 66631}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely everyone\", \"from\": 66633, \"to\": 66652}, {\"ngram\": \"that table\", \"from\": 66670, \"to\": 66680}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 66699, \"to\": 66703}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 66707, \"to\": 66715}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 66728, \"to\": 66732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is ambiguity and cowardice writ large.Mankind's only wallagainst the encroachment of the barbarian is the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 66733, \"to\": 66861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66845, \"end\": 66860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999612444989, \"rank\": 3.693612044150683e-08, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ambiguity\", \"from\": 66742, \"to\": 66751}, {\"ngram\": \"writ\", \"from\": 66766, \"to\": 66770}, {\"ngram\": \"Mankind\", \"from\": 66777, \"to\": 66784}, {\"ngram\": \"the encroachment\", \"from\": 66804, \"to\": 66820}, {\"ngram\": \"the barbarian\", \"from\": 66824, \"to\": 66837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She alone can return a voice to the oppressed of the Woke Leviathan.In A.D. 452, it was only one year after Pope Leo the Great valiantly defended the hypostatic union of Christ our Savior against the heretic Eutyches.With that monumental task barely completed, he confronted still another crisis besetting the Roman world: the attack of Attila the Hun.\", \"from\": 66862, \"to\": 67214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66915, \"end\": 66919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6467283854270933e-17, \"text\": \"Woke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\"}, {\"begin\": 66975, \"end\": 66978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"score\": 0.9964405031691338, \"rank\": 0.0035721312743149385, \"text\": \"Leo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\"}, {\"begin\": 67172, \"end\": 67177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9942112456188104, \"rank\": 0.005791400383446156, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 67199, \"end\": 67205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.225434866971743e-25, \"text\": \"Attila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a voice\", \"from\": 66883, \"to\": 66890}, {\"ngram\": \"the oppressed\", \"from\": 66894, \"to\": 66907}, {\"ngram\": \"A.D.\", \"from\": 66933, \"to\": 66937}, {\"ngram\": \"the Great\", \"from\": 66979, \"to\": 66988}, {\"ngram\": \"the hypostatic union\", \"from\": 67008, \"to\": 67028}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 67032, \"to\": 67038}, {\"ngram\": \"our Savior\", \"from\": 67039, \"to\": 67049}, {\"ngram\": \"the heretic Eutyches\", \"from\": 67058, \"to\": 67078}, {\"ngram\": \"that monumental task\", \"from\": 67084, \"to\": 67104}, {\"ngram\": \"another crisis\", \"from\": 67143, \"to\": 67157}, {\"ngram\": \"the attack\", \"from\": 67185, \"to\": 67195}, {\"ngram\": \"the Hun\", \"from\": 67206, \"to\": 67213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His frightful hordes had decimated much of the former Roman Empire, with its legacy of high civilization and culture.\", \"from\": 67215, \"to\": 67332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67269, \"end\": 67281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9897904676140601, \"rank\": 0.01017165184587759, \"text\": \"Roman Empire\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His frightful hordes\", \"from\": 67215, \"to\": 67235}, {\"ngram\": \"its legacy\", \"from\": 67288, \"to\": 67298}, {\"ngram\": \"high civilization\", \"from\": 67302, \"to\": 67319}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 67324, \"to\": 67331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now that barbarian was at the very gates of Rome.\", \"from\": 67333, \"to\": 67382, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67377, \"end\": 67381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.7937174410543635, \"rank\": 0.1098575344182588, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"barbarian\", \"from\": 67342, \"to\": 67351}, {\"ngram\": \"the very gates\", \"from\": 67359, \"to\": 67373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All seemed to be lost.\", \"from\": 67383, \"to\": 67405, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pope Leo the Great, in solemn procession with priests, deacons, and acolytes swinging golden thuribles, went out to meet the bloodthirsty chieftain.\", \"from\": 67406, \"to\": 67554, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Great\", \"from\": 67415, \"to\": 67424}, {\"ngram\": \"solemn procession\", \"from\": 67429, \"to\": 67446}, {\"ngram\": \"priests\", \"from\": 67452, \"to\": 67459}, {\"ngram\": \"deacons\", \"from\": 67461, \"to\": 67468}, {\"ngram\": \"golden thuribles\", \"from\": 67492, \"to\": 67508}, {\"ngram\": \"the bloodthirsty chieftain\", \"from\": 67527, \"to\": 67553}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Face-to-face, they spoke.\", \"from\": 67555, \"to\": 67580, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"face\", \"from\": 67563, \"to\": 67567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After a brief conversation, Attila turned around and commanded his troops to retreat.\", \"from\": 67581, \"to\": 67666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67609, \"end\": 67615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.297379903438159e-22, \"text\": \"Attila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brief conversation\", \"from\": 67587, \"to\": 67607}, {\"ngram\": \"his troops\", \"from\": 67644, \"to\": 67654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rome was saved.\", \"from\": 67667, \"to\": 67682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67667, \"end\": 67671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.7937174410543635, \"rank\": 0.1098575344182588, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Christianity was saved.\", \"from\": 67683, \"to\": 67706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67683, \"end\": 67695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7042718742905274, \"rank\": 0.41810139554794495, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Civilization could breathe again.And Leo became known to the ages as \\\"the Great.\", \"from\": 67707, \"to\": 67787, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67744, \"end\": 67747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"score\": 0.9981094141654927, \"rank\": 0.0018941469714921903, \"text\": \"Leo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Civilization\", \"from\": 67707, \"to\": 67719}, {\"ngram\": \"the ages\", \"from\": 67764, \"to\": 67772}, {\"ngram\": \"the Great\", \"from\": 67777, \"to\": 67786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Only the Catholic Church can save mankind from the barbarians-whether it be from Attila or the Parisians of the 2024 Olympic Games.So, we wait.AuthorFr.\", \"from\": 67787, \"to\": 67940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67797, \"end\": 67812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999002522009524, \"rank\": 9.975648867416108e-05, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 67869, \"end\": 67875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.297379903438159e-22, \"text\": \"Attila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mankind\", \"from\": 67822, \"to\": 67829}, {\"ngram\": \"the barbarians\", \"from\": 67835, \"to\": 67849}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parisians\", \"from\": 67879, \"to\": 67892}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 67896, \"to\": 67918}, {\"ngram\": \"AuthorFr\", \"from\": 67931, \"to\": 67939}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John A. PerriconeFr.\", \"from\": 67941, \"to\": 67961, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John A. PerriconeFr\", \"from\": 67941, \"to\": 67960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John A. Perricone, Ph.D., is an adjunct professor of philosophy at Iona University in New Rochelle, New York.\", \"from\": 67962, \"to\": 68071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 68029, \"end\": 68033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\", \"score\": 0.8079619839724143, \"rank\": 0.1891294087151664, \"text\": \"Iona\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iona_College\"}, {\"begin\": 68048, \"end\": 68070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Rochelle, New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\"}, {\"begin\": 68048, \"end\": 68070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New Rochelle, New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Rochelle,_New_York\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John A. Perricone\", \"from\": 67962, \"to\": 67979}, {\"ngram\": \"Ph.D.\", \"from\": 67981, \"to\": 67986}, {\"ngram\": \"an adjunct professor\", \"from\": 67991, \"to\": 68011}, {\"ngram\": \"philosophy\", \"from\": 68015, \"to\": 68025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His articles have appeared inSt.\", \"from\": 68072, \"to\": 68104, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His articles\", \"from\": 68072, \"to\": 68084}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John's Law Review, The Latin Mass, New Oxford ReviewandThe Journal of Catholic Legal Studies.He can be reached atwww.fatherperricone.com.\", \"from\": 68105, \"to\": 68242, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John's Law Review\", \"from\": 68105, \"to\": 68122}, {\"ngram\": \"The Latin Mass\", \"from\": 68124, \"to\": 68138}, {\"ngram\": \"New Oxford ReviewandThe Journal\", \"from\": 68140, \"to\": 68171}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholic Legal Studies\", \"from\": 68175, \"to\": 68197}, {\"ngram\": \"atwww.fatherperricone.com\", \"from\": 68216, \"to\": 68241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those manic forces were kept at bay by the might of the Church.\", \"from\": 68244, \"to\": 68307, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those manic forces\", \"from\": 68244, \"to\": 68262}, {\"ngram\": \"bay\", \"from\": 68276, \"to\": 68279}, {\"ngram\": \"the might\", \"from\": 68283, \"to\": 68292}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 68296, \"to\": 68306}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And that doctrinal roar bellowed with no uncertainty, and with one universal voice.\", \"from\": 68308, \"to\": 68391, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"And that doctrinal roar\", \"from\": 68308, \"to\": 68331}, {\"ngram\": \"no uncertainty\", \"from\": 68346, \"to\": 68360}, {\"ngram\": \"one universal voice\", \"from\": 68371, \"to\": 68390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The World would find no cracks in the solidity of the Church's voice in those sturdier days.\", \"from\": 68392, \"to\": 68484, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The World\", \"from\": 68392, \"to\": 68401}, {\"ngram\": \"no cracks\", \"from\": 68413, \"to\": 68422}, {\"ngram\": \"the solidity\", \"from\": 68426, \"to\": 68438}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 68442, \"to\": 68460}, {\"ngram\": \"those sturdier days\", \"from\": 68464, \"to\": 68483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Contrary voices would indeed bay, but they had no illusions about the impregnable bastions of the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 68485, \"to\": 68599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 68583, \"end\": 68598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999956405237737, \"rank\": 3.866671429497124e-06, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Contrary voices\", \"from\": 68485, \"to\": 68500}, {\"ngram\": \"no illusions\", \"from\": 68532, \"to\": 68544}, {\"ngram\": \"the impregnable bastions\", \"from\": 68551, \"to\": 68575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They might have found shelter in a renegade priest or shepherd here or there, but those of that ilk were conspicuous in their paucity.Blasphemy on such a grand scale as the Opening Ceremonies of the Paris Olympics would have been unthinkable.\", \"from\": 68600, \"to\": 68842, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"shelter\", \"from\": 68622, \"to\": 68629}, {\"ngram\": \"a renegade priest\", \"from\": 68633, \"to\": 68650}, {\"ngram\": \"shepherd\", \"from\": 68654, \"to\": 68662}, {\"ngram\": \"that ilk\", \"from\": 68691, \"to\": 68699}, {\"ngram\": \"their paucity\", \"from\": 68720, \"to\": 68733}, {\"ngram\": \"Blasphemy\", \"from\": 68734, \"to\": 68743}, {\"ngram\": \"such a grand scale\", \"from\": 68747, \"to\": 68765}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 68769, \"to\": 68791}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 68795, \"to\": 68813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, Napolean kidnapped Pope Pius VII in 1809, dragging him across the Alps in precarious health to Fontainebleau.\", \"from\": 68843, \"to\": 68957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 68943, \"end\": 68956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"score\": 0.996630494128782, \"rank\": 0.0033808970807305237, \"text\": \"Fontainebleau\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fontainebleau\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Pope Pius VII\", \"from\": 68867, \"to\": 68880}, {\"ngram\": \"the Alps\", \"from\": 68910, \"to\": 68918}, {\"ngram\": \"precarious health\", \"from\": 68922, \"to\": 68939}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Italian armies captured Rome in 1859, forcing Blessed Pius IX to flee the Eternal City to the city of Gaeta.\", \"from\": 68958, \"to\": 69074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 68966, \"end\": 68973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.775082692482548, \"rank\": 0.19651798319446206, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 68990, \"end\": 68994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.6559403156576921, \"rank\": 0.4921957911872365, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 69068, \"end\": 69073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"score\": 0.9999999998483418, \"rank\": 1.5168369728912712e-10, \"text\": \"Gaeta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaeta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Blessed Pius IX\", \"from\": 69012, \"to\": 69027}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eternal City\", \"from\": 69036, \"to\": 69052}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 69056, \"to\": 69064}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But all these depredations could not approach the collapse that the Opening Ceremonies presage.\", \"from\": 69075, \"to\": 69170, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all these depredations\", \"from\": 69079, \"to\": 69101}, {\"ngram\": \"the collapse\", \"from\": 69121, \"to\": 69133}, {\"ngram\": \"the Opening Ceremonies\", \"from\": 69139, \"to\": 69161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Church was assaulted and the popes harassed, the foundations of human dignity and Western Civilization were not threatened.\", \"from\": 69171, \"to\": 69304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 69263, \"end\": 69283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.6048736184562169, \"rank\": 0.6532379153058226, \"text\": \"Western Civilization\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 69177, \"to\": 69187}, {\"ngram\": \"the popes\", \"from\": 69206, \"to\": 69215}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundations\", \"from\": 69226, \"to\": 69241}, {\"ngram\": \"human dignity\", \"from\": 69245, \"to\": 69258}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Church, even with her popes in captivity, would see to that.Enemies of all that is good and true and beautiful have found their opening in the decades-long attenuation of the Church's voice.\", \"from\": 69305, \"to\": 69499, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Church\", \"from\": 69305, \"to\": 69315}, {\"ngram\": \"her popes\", \"from\": 69327, \"to\": 69336}, {\"ngram\": \"captivity\", \"from\": 69340, \"to\": 69349}, {\"ngram\": \"Enemies\", \"from\": 69369, \"to\": 69376}, {\"ngram\": \"their opening\", \"from\": 69431, \"to\": 69444}, {\"ngram\": \"the decades-long attenuation\", \"from\": 69448, \"to\": 69476}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 69480, \"to\": 69498}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have seen all too clearly the Church's d\\u00e9tente with the spirit of the world and exploited a perfect opportunity.\", \"from\": 69500, \"to\": 69617, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church's d\\u00e9tente\", \"from\": 69531, \"to\": 69551}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 69557, \"to\": 69567}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 69571, \"to\": 69580}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect opportunity\", \"from\": 69595, \"to\": 69616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the victory they awaited for so long, and now it was handed to them on a silver platter.\", \"from\": 69618, \"to\": 69713, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the victory\", \"from\": 69625, \"to\": 69636}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver platter\", \"from\": 69696, \"to\": 69712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How else to interpret Archbishop Paglia, president of the Pontifical Academy for Life, defending the Olympic Last Supper depiction \\\"as revealing a profound question: everyone, absolutely everyone, wants to sit at that table where Jesus gives life to everyone and teaches love.\", \"from\": 69714, \"to\": 69990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 69736, \"end\": 69746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9998315006711743, \"rank\": 0.00014343961781930275, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 69944, \"end\": 69949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9376345309791523, \"rank\": 0.06651353793521567, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 69755, \"to\": 69764}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pontifical Academy\", \"from\": 69768, \"to\": 69790}, {\"ngram\": \"Life\", \"from\": 69795, \"to\": 69799}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Last Supper depiction\", \"from\": 69811, \"to\": 69844}, {\"ngram\": \"a profound question\", \"from\": 69859, \"to\": 69878}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 69880, \"to\": 69888}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely everyone\", \"from\": 69890, \"to\": 69909}, {\"ngram\": \"that table\", \"from\": 69927, \"to\": 69937}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 69956, \"to\": 69960}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 69964, \"to\": 69972}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 69985, \"to\": 69989}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is ambiguity and cowardice writ large.Mankind's only wallagainst the encroachment of the barbarian is the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 69990, \"to\": 70118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 70102, \"end\": 70117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999996306908769, \"rank\": 3.685228861003656e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ambiguity\", \"from\": 69999, \"to\": 70008}, {\"ngram\": \"writ\", \"from\": 70023, \"to\": 70027}, {\"ngram\": \"Mankind\", \"from\": 70034, \"to\": 70041}, {\"ngram\": \"the encroachment\", \"from\": 70061, \"to\": 70077}, {\"ngram\": \"the barbarian\", \"from\": 70081, \"to\": 70094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She alone can return a voice to the oppressed of the Woke Leviathan.In A.D. 452, it was only one year after Pope Leo the Great valiantly defended the hypostatic union of Christ our Savior against the heretic Eutyches.With that monumental task barely completed, he confronted still another crisis besetting the Roman world: the attack of Attila the Hun.\", \"from\": 70119, \"to\": 70471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 70172, \"end\": 70176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0463722331013693e-17, \"text\": \"Woke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\"}, {\"begin\": 70232, \"end\": 70235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"score\": 0.9960339859762929, \"rank\": 0.003981766224953393, \"text\": \"Leo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\"}, {\"begin\": 70429, \"end\": 70434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9967505588789237, \"rank\": 0.00325647374570835, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 70456, \"end\": 70462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8812687040316797e-27, \"text\": \"Attila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a voice\", \"from\": 70140, \"to\": 70147}, {\"ngram\": \"the oppressed\", \"from\": 70151, \"to\": 70164}, {\"ngram\": \"A.D.\", \"from\": 70190, \"to\": 70194}, {\"ngram\": \"the Great\", \"from\": 70236, \"to\": 70245}, {\"ngram\": \"the hypostatic union\", \"from\": 70265, \"to\": 70285}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 70289, \"to\": 70295}, {\"ngram\": \"our Savior\", \"from\": 70296, \"to\": 70306}, {\"ngram\": \"the heretic Eutyches\", \"from\": 70315, \"to\": 70335}, {\"ngram\": \"that monumental task\", \"from\": 70341, \"to\": 70361}, {\"ngram\": \"another crisis\", \"from\": 70400, \"to\": 70414}, {\"ngram\": \"the attack\", \"from\": 70442, \"to\": 70452}, {\"ngram\": \"the Hun\", \"from\": 70463, \"to\": 70470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His frightful hordes had decimated much of the former Roman Empire, with its legacy of high civilization and culture.\", \"from\": 70472, \"to\": 70589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 70526, \"end\": 70538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9988018247014834, \"rank\": 0.0011949342846063091, \"text\": \"Roman Empire\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His frightful hordes\", \"from\": 70472, \"to\": 70492}, {\"ngram\": \"its legacy\", \"from\": 70545, \"to\": 70555}, {\"ngram\": \"high civilization\", \"from\": 70559, \"to\": 70576}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 70581, \"to\": 70588}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now that barbarian was at the very gates of Rome.\", \"from\": 70590, \"to\": 70639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 70634, \"end\": 70638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.778066255660429, \"rank\": 0.21013308