f human dignity and Western Civilization were not threatened.\", \"from\": 71938, \"to\": 72071, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 72030, \"end\": 72050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"score\": 0.7386284958005325, \"rank\": 0.3538605749513407, \"text\": \"Western Civilization\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_world\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 71944, \"to\": 71954}, {\"ngram\": \"the popes\", \"from\": 71973, \"to\": 71982}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundations\", \"from\": 71993, \"to\": 72008}, {\"ngram\": \"human dignity\", \"from\": 72012, \"to\": 72025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Church, even with her popes in captivity, would see to that.Enemies of all that is good and true and beautiful have found their opening in the decades-long attenuation of the Church's voice.\", \"from\": 72072, \"to\": 72266, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Church\", \"from\": 72072, \"to\": 72082}, {\"ngram\": \"her popes\", \"from\": 72094, \"to\": 72103}, {\"ngram\": \"captivity\", \"from\": 72107, \"to\": 72116}, {\"ngram\": \"Enemies\", \"from\": 72136, \"to\": 72143}, {\"ngram\": \"their opening\", \"from\": 72198, \"to\": 72211}, {\"ngram\": \"the decades-long attenuation\", \"from\": 72215, \"to\": 72243}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church's voice\", \"from\": 72247, \"to\": 72265}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have seen all too clearly the Church's d\\u00e9tente with the spirit of the world and exploited a perfect opportunity.\", \"from\": 72267, \"to\": 72384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Church's d\\u00e9tente\", \"from\": 72298, \"to\": 72318}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 72324, \"to\": 72334}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 72338, \"to\": 72347}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect opportunity\", \"from\": 72362, \"to\": 72383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the victory they awaited for so long, and now it was handed to them on a silver platter.\", \"from\": 72385, \"to\": 72480, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the victory\", \"from\": 72392, \"to\": 72403}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver platter\", \"from\": 72463, \"to\": 72479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How else to interpret Archbishop Paglia, president of the Pontifical Academy for Life, defending the Olympic Last Supper depiction \\\"as revealing a profound question: everyone, absolutely everyone, wants to sit at that table where Jesus gives life to everyone and teaches love.\", \"from\": 72481, \"to\": 72757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 72503, \"end\": 72513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9997419926649607, \"rank\": 0.00012916645659966655, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 72711, \"end\": 72716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.619382372887062, \"rank\": 0.6145019700377441, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 72522, \"to\": 72531}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pontifical Academy\", \"from\": 72535, \"to\": 72557}, {\"ngram\": \"Life\", \"from\": 72562, \"to\": 72566}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Last Supper depiction\", \"from\": 72578, \"to\": 72611}, {\"ngram\": \"a profound question\", \"from\": 72626, \"to\": 72645}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 72647, \"to\": 72655}, {\"ngram\": \"absolutely everyone\", \"from\": 72657, \"to\": 72676}, {\"ngram\": \"that table\", \"from\": 72694, \"to\": 72704}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 72723, \"to\": 72727}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 72731, \"to\": 72739}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 72752, \"to\": 72756}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is ambiguity and cowardice writ large.Mankind's only wallagainst the encroachment of the barbarian is the Catholic Church.\", \"from\": 72757, \"to\": 72885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 72869, \"end\": 72884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999992725303545, \"rank\": 5.679986406734903e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ambiguity\", \"from\": 72766, \"to\": 72775}, {\"ngram\": \"writ\", \"from\": 72790, \"to\": 72794}, {\"ngram\": \"Mankind\", \"from\": 72801, \"to\": 72808}, {\"ngram\": \"the encroachment\", \"from\": 72828, \"to\": 72844}, {\"ngram\": \"the barbarian\", \"from\": 72848, \"to\": 72861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She alone can return a voice to the oppressed of the Woke Leviathan.In A.D. 452, it was only one year after Pope Leo the Great valiantly defended the hypostatic union of Christ our Savior against the heretic Eutyches.With that monumental task barely completed, he confronted still another crisis besetting the Roman world: the attack of Attila the Hun.\", \"from\": 72886, \"to\": 73238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 72939, \"end\": 72943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.291230735885765e-16, \"text\": \"Woke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Woke\"}, {\"begin\": 72999, \"end\": 73002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"score\": 0.9999844888821097, \"rank\": 1.5511288252685733e-05, \"text\": \"Leo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Phokas_the_Younger\"}, {\"begin\": 73196, \"end\": 73201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.9954923038096594, \"rank\": 0.004522005895888266, \"text\